law.text:
An individual is eligible for the Program if the individual:
Has a cognitive, sensory, or physical disability;
Is at least 18 years old and under the age of 65 years at the time of enrollment;
Requires the level of care provided in a nursing facility;
Will be discharged or diverted from a nursing facility;
Qualifies for the Medicaid home and community-based waiver services for adults with physical disabilities;
Has a functional need; and
Has income that does not exceed 300% of Supplemental Security Income.
